citeinfo.title: Walrus Islands Closure

descript.abstract: Description of Area: From April 1 through September 30 of any fishing year, all fishing vessels are prohibited in the area between 3 and 12 nautical miles around islands named Round Island and The Twins and around Cape Peirce (58°33’ N. latitude, 161°43’ W. longitude).
descript.purpose: Minimizes vessel interaction with walrus around haul-out sites in northern Bristol Bay.
descript.supplinf: Origin: Permanently established under Amendment 17 on April 24, 1992.
